mentation of the e-commerce solution for our customers (Resellers). Responsibilities: Pre-analysis, selection and implementation of the solution. Including building basic data for the solution.Responsibility for internal computer systems and building infrastructure based on Compaq servers and Windows 2000 Server. Including firewall, VPN solutions and new mail system.Product ManagerSupply Services A/S2000  –  2002 (2 years)I was Product Manager for the Macromedia Software Brand and som other smaller software brands.E-Business ManagerHeliogruppen A/S2000  –  2001 (1 year)Project participant in the creation of e-commerce solution for selling IT products. Responsibilities in the project were: Sales Interface, logistics part and full interconnection with the existing ERP system and IT environment.Participation in marketing planning for the launch of e-commerce solution.Management and budget responsibility for logistics department, including Warehouse, purchasing and customer service. A total of 8 people.Sales Manager / Logistic ManagerHeliogruppen1999  –  2000 (1 year)I managed a small inbound sales department with 6 sales people.This included preparation of budgets and monitoring and reporting in relation to these.I was also responsible for procurement for the entire company and toke care of the warehouse with 4 employes.During this period the company acquired an additional 2 companies that were merged into Heliogruppen Denmark.Key Account ManagerGreenHouse A/S1998  –  1999 (1 year)Part owner of the company GreenHouse A/S after a peaceful Management-Buy-Out from SystemForum A/S in july 1998.The company was sold again in October 1999 to HelioGruppen Norway and changes name to HelioGruppen Denmark A/S.Gross margin budget 1998: 2.850.000 DKKAccount ManagerSystemForum A/S1997  –  1998 (1 year)Apple Center GreenHouse became a division in SystemForum and I continued working with Sales of graphic IT solutions for the media industry.Gross margin budget 1997: 2.520.000 DKKApple 